Key Match Events: Emmanuel Rivera went 4 for 4 with two homers and four RBIs to lead the Baltimore Orioles to a 9-2 win over the Minnesota Twins.
Ryan O’Hearn hit a two-run home run during the first inning.
Jackson Holliday added three hits for the Orioles.
Ryan Jeffers hit a two-run homer with two outs in the ninth to help the Twins avoid a shutout.
Matt Bowman started as the opener for the Orioles and got the first four outs.
Tucker Davidson allowed four hits over 4 2/3 shutout innings to earn the victory.
Zebby Matthews allowed six runs on seven hits with three walks and five strikeouts in three innings.
Post-Match Reflections: Orioles manager Brandon Hyde expressed encouragement about the team's performance going into the postseason.
Twins manager Rocco Baldelli commented on Zebby Matthews' rapid ascent through the minor leagues and his potential for the rotation next spring.
Emmanuel Rivera reflected on his performance, stating it was a special night for him.
Others: The Orioles have clinched the top wild card in the American League and will face either the Kansas City Royals or Detroit Tigers in the first round of the playoffs.
The Twins have been eliminated from playoff contention.
